If race overfills, same owner entries must prefer a horse at the time of entry. No nomination. An entry fee of $250 due at time of entry. Weights: 3 years old .124 Older .126. .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SANTALUZ DREAMIN Challenged lead three wide in opening stages, moved up to confront leaders outside, came clearly into fray approaching quarter pole along two path, cleared to the wire. DEFENSE WINS Held up five wide into the first turn, strunger further out to the seven path backstretch, assumed a three wide bid into turn and steadily improved into stretch, no match for the winner. STAY HAPPY Stalked off the pace four wide, move upd between foes into far turn, flattened late. MORE HONOR Tucked in second flight on rail, asked at quarter pole to improve, idled for a furlong before showing late gain between tiring competition. RINGS OF SATURN Led inside early, joined at half-mile pole by gaining rivals, backed out into far turn, moved evenly to wire.
